# Example preference — DELETE or replace me

This is a format example. A real preference file is short and specific — the standing rules you'd otherwise repeat every time you touch this technology/feature.

Trigger (add to `.claude/preferences/INDEX.md`):
`| Railway deploy, railway.json, scale-to-zero | .claude/preferences/railway.md |`

Example content for a `railway.md`:

- Prefer Railway with **scale-to-zero**, a **European region** (e.g. `europe-west4`), and the service URL prefixed with the project name.
- `railway.json` `build.watchPatterns` must exclude `docs/`, `tests/`, `.claude/`, `.github/`, and markdown so doc/spec commits don't trigger redeploys.
- Verify a deploy is healthy via the Railway MCP before considering a release done.

Replace this file with your own preferences, and delete this example once you have real ones.
